**who —** THE SPONGE — a life-science sphere — the brainless mind

**what —** An animal with no neurons, no muscles, no organs, no symmetry — just a colony of cells pumping water through a living filter. Yet it contracts, 'sneezes' to clear its pores, and, if pushed through a sieve into single cells, will crawl back together and rebuild itself. The other floor of animal life, beside Trichoplax.

**where —** intelligence without a brain  Framework inputs: the living; the rule; the signal; the open question  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** An animal with no neurons, no muscles, no organs, no symmetry — just a colony of cells pumping water through a living filter. Yet it contracts, 'sneezes' to clear its pores, and, if pushed through a sieve into single cells, will crawl back together and rebuild itself. The other floor of animal life, beside Trichoplax.

**how —** Crystallized from the public record of the science.

**◌ the mythos —** An animal with no neurons, no muscles, no organs, no symmetry — just a colony of cells pumping water through a living filter. Yet it contracts, 'sneezes' to clear its pores, and, if pushed through a sieve into single cells, will crawl back together and rebuild itself. The other floor of animal life, beside Trichoplax. where a mind appears with no neurons in it

